1. Create command line interface for this utility.
    1.1. Create console_helper with interface features.
        1.1.1. Different color output support. (+)
        1.1.2. Divide console for multiple output.
    1.2. Input parameters: (+)
        - XLGYRO_TRAILER_SIZE, default (0x04). (+)
        - XLGYRO_TRAILER_VALUE, default (0xA5). (+)
        - XLGYRO_PREAMBULE_VALUE, default (0xAA55). (+)
        - DEFAULT_DEVIATION_HI, default (300.0). (+)
        - DEFAULT_DEVIATION_LO, default (-300.0). (+)
        - Z_AXIS_THD_HI, default (0.4). (+)
        - Z_AXIS_THD_LO, default (-0.4). (+)
        - ROAD_QUALITY, default (3) "NORMAL". (+)
    1.3. Create menu and safe exit. (+)


2. Create API for generating and sending messages in required format to 127.0.0.1:11333.
    2.1. Create required struct to send XLGYRO_PACKET_STRUCT. (+)
    2.2. Create TCP server on 127.0.0.1:11333 to send messages. (+)
    2.3. Create random generator of pits existence. (+)
        2.3.1. Generate also random gyroscope data to analyse if pit exist. (+)
        2.3.2. Add to generator a `chance` proerty, which will define how many pits can be.
